      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You've touched on a crucial point regarding inconsistent application of political terminology. Many critiques suggest the \"failure\" label is often a rhetorical tool used when the anticipated normative benefits—like liberal democratization—don't materialize on schedule. This double standard arises because the goals of intervention are often idealistic, whereas the realpolitik outcomes are inherently messy and unpredictable. Therefore, the label often reflects the gap between optimistic strategic *intent* and complex geopolitical *reality*.",
      "source": "target",
